# Secrets and Credentials

- Never commit API keys, tokens, passwords, or raw credentials to source control.
- Never log raw secrets in terminal output, API responses, or UI error states.
- Validate external credential inputs early and return actionable non-secret error messages.
- Keep all provider credential writes on server routes; do not expose secrets in client payload echoes.
- Prefer environment variables and secure credential stores for runtime access.
